President Biden has declared a major disaster in the State of New York due to the remnants of Tropical Storm Fred. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures in certain counties. Laia Sun Yee has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Further information can be obtained by contacting the FEMA News Desk.